{{ProductPage|http://web.archive.org/web/20120109083533/http://www.asus.com/Networks/Wireless_Adapters/WL330}} ''(via archive.org)'' The '''ASUS''' logo and "WL-330 R1.71" is silkscreened on the FCC EUT's board. The '''TERAYON''' MAP-11B would appear to be using the same board. It's mentioned in the FCC test report. Default settings in this entry are per the FCC manual. ==Probable used PSU(s)== The power supply shown in the FCC photos is an unbranded FA040-1000. {{hasPowerSupply |brand=unknown |model=FA040-1000 |input_v=100-240 |input_c=AC |input_hz=50/60 |input_conn=NEMA 1-15P |output_v=4 |output_a=1 |output_c=DC |output_conn=barrel |manuf_country=Taiwan |style=small, straight }}
